{"title_page": "NAC TV", "text_new": "{{short description|Community television station}}\n{{Infobox broadcast |\n  call_letters             = CH5248|\n  station_logo             = Naclogo.png |\n  station_slogan           = NAC TV|\n  station_branding         = |\n  analog                   = 30 ([[UHF]])<br/>[[Cable television|Cable]]: 12 ([[VHF]])|\n  digital                  = |\n  other_chs                = |\n  affiliations             = |\n  founded                  = 1978 (cable)<br>1983 (over-the-air)<br/> 2012 (regional)|\n  location                 = [[Neepawa, Manitoba]]|\n  callsign_meaning         = Sequentially assigned by the CRTC|\n  former_callsigns         = |\n  owner                    = Neepawa Access Community Television (NACTV) Inc.|\n  former_affiliations      = |\n  effective_radiated_power = 100 [[watt|W]]|\n  homepage                 = [http://nactv.tv/ NAC TV Official Website]|\n}}\n\n'''NAC TV''' (''Neepawa Access Community Television'') is a [[Community channel (Canada)|community channel]] based in [[Neepawa, Manitoba]]. It is available on local cable provider [[Westman Communications Group|Westman Cable]] channel 12, [[terrestrial television|broadcasts over the air]] on MTS channel 30 and also on Bell ExpressVu channel 592. \n\n==History==\nNAC TV became available across Manitoba on [[MTS TV]] in October 2012.  NAC is on Channel 30 on the MTS lineup.<ref>[http://www.mywestman.ca/community-news/132-nac-tv-now-live-on-mts-tv.html NAC-TV now live on MTS TV]</ref><ref>[https://www.mts.ca/mts/personal/tv/tv+channel?ChannelID=295e07268b65a310VgnVCM1000002a040f0a____&RatePlan=HD%20Daph%20Standard NAC TV Channel 30]</ref>  NAC TV is also carried by [[Bell TV]], channel 592, since late 2012.<ref>[http://tvonline.bell.ca/tvonline/servlet/CommandServlet?command=flow&processid=167&simpleSearchKeyWord=null&requestedPage=0&requestedSortMethod=3&requestedSearchMethod=0&simpleSearchSelectedResultTitle=NAC%20TV%20Neepawa&simpleSearchSelectedResultEpisodeTitle=null&occurences=1&prevRequestedPageNum=95&prevRequestedSortMethod=7 Bell TV]</ref><ref>[http://www.mywestman.ca/community-news/59-date-pushed-back-as-to-when-nac-tv-goes-live-on-bell-expressvu.html Date pushed back as to when NAC-TV goes live on Bell ExpressVu]</ref>\n\nIn addition to airing local town council meetings, the station also airs live bingo, local news and public affairs shows, [[curling]] (currently absent from being shown) and [[hockey]] matches, plus ethnic, religious, children's cartoons, and special interest programs, totaling 55 hours per week of local programming. Scheduled programming runs from about 10am to 11pm each day;<ref>[http://nactv.ca/pdf/listing.pdf Schedule example]</ref> at other times, the station operates as a community billboard.\n\n\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Community channel (Canada)]]\n* [[Public access]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.crtc.gc.ca/eng/archive/2005/db2005-293.htm CRTC Decision 2005-293 - 2005-2012 License Renewal]\n\n{{clear}}\n{{Brandon TV}}\n{{CanindTVstations}}\n\n[[Category:Canadian community channels]]\n[[Category:Television stations in Manitoba]]\n[[Category:Television channels and stations established in 1978]]\n[[Category:1978 establishments in Manitoba]]\n\n\n{{Canada-tv-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox broadcast |\n  call_letters             = CH5248|\n  station_logo             = Naclogo.png |\n  station_slogan           = NAC TV|\n  station_branding         = |\n  analog                   = 30 ([[UHF]])<br/>[[Cable television|Cable]]: 12 ([[VHF]])|\n  digital                  = |\n  other_chs                = |\n  affiliations             = |\n  founded                  = 1978 (cable)<br>1983 (over-the-air)<br/> 2012 (regional)|\n  location                 = [[Neepawa, Manitoba]]|\n  callsign_meaning         = Sequentially assigned by the CRTC|\n  former_callsigns         = |\n  owner                    = Neepawa Access Community Television (NACTV) Inc.|\n